The Vice President of the United States spoke with First Minister Robinson and Deputy First Minister McGuinness of Northern Ireland to support the launch of an All-Party Group process aimed at addressing sensitive issues in Northern Ireland, such as parades, protests, flags, symbols, emblems, and dealing with the past. The Vice President expressed concern about violence and attacks related to parades and supported calls for calm and respect for the rule of law. He also pledged the full support of the United States and his personal support to Dr. Richard Haass, the chair of the All-Party Group process. The Vice President emphasized the importance of tackling these sensitive issues to create lasting peace and prosperity for all in Northern Ireland.